Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. Mild hyperchloremia and elevated triglycerides are present. Alkaline phosphatase is slightly below the reference range but likely not clinically significant. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal function.
